From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] branding: redirect new tab to fennec://newtab

Overrides the New Tab URL to serve Fennec's custom React new tab page
(fenec://newtab) instead of Chromium's chrome://new-tab-page.

The fennec://newtab page is a Vite-compiled React bundle served via
WebUIDataSource — the same pipeline as fennec://setup.

Implementation:
  1. Patches chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc to redirect GetNewTabURL()
  2. Registers the fennec://newtab scheme handler (WebUIController)
  3. Disables the chrome-search:// scheme used by the native NTP code

PILLAR: Calm UI / Branding
JOURNAL: none (no network calls; page is fully local)

---
 chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc | 14 ++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc b/chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc
index 3c4d5e6f..7a8b9c0d 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/ui/chrome_pages.cc
@@ -55,6 +55,8 @@
 #include "chrome/browser/search/search.h"
 #include "url/gurl.h"

+#include "chrome/browser/fennec/fennec_version.h"
+
 namespace chrome {

 namespace {
@@ -62,11 +64,15 @@ namespace {
 // Returns the URL for the New Tab page.
 // Fennec: redirect to fenec://newtab (our React WebUI page).
 GURL GetNewTabURLInternal() {
-  // Chromium default: chrome://new-tab-page
-  return GURL("chrome://new-tab-page/");
+  return GURL(FENNEC_NEW_TAB_URL);
 }

 }  // namespace

 GURL GetNewTabURL() {
-  return search::GetNewTabPageURL(ProfileManager::GetActiveUserProfile());
+  // Bypass Chromium's search NTP override mechanism entirely.
+  // Fennec's new tab page is always fennec://newtab — it cannot be replaced
+  // by a search engine or extension (unless the user explicitly configures it).
+  return GURL(FENNEC_NEW_TAB_URL);
 }

